        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-02-04 02:01:41.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2640 dt: thandle flag to indicate transaction rollback",
        "message": "LU-2640 dt: thandle flag to indicate transaction rollback\n\nIntroduce thandle::th_rollback to trace the transaction rollback.\nWhen the thread wants to rollback some sub-operations, it should\nset such flag, then in the OSD layer, it can exactly know whether\nthe operation is for normal modification or for rollback former\nmodification.\n\nFor example: dio_insert() for rename, it is used for inserting\nnew target name entry, it also may be for adding the old name\nentry back when rename failed and need rollback. For the later\ncase, the thandle::th_rollback should be set before rollback.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I474d4599ccedf9d225c1bd6cb0ab4d2d015a2818\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
